<subSubSection pageId="181" pageNumber="182" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="181.[151,1437,1122,1329]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">
This family of Orthorrhapha contains 786 species found worldwide; however, its taxonomic boundaries are under debate (
<bibRefCitation author="Marshall, S. A." box="[240,408,1195,1221]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" refId="ref358584" refString="Marshall, S. A. (2012) Flies. The natural history and diversity of Diptera. Firefly Books, Richmond Hill, 616 pp." type="book" year="2012">Marshall 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T." box="[420,686,1195,1221]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" refId="ref350035" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. &amp; Pape, T. (2020) Systema Dipterorum. Version 2. 7. Available from: http: // www. diptera. org / (accessed 30 August 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Evenhuis &amp; Pape 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In his “ 
<emphasis box="[790,984,1195,1221]" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">
Familia 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" box="[886,984,1195,1220]" class="Arachnida" family="Leptinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Leptinae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
”, rather than in the family 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="James" baseAuthorityYear="1968" box="[1295,1437,1195,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Rhagionidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Rhagionidae</taxonomicName>
proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Latreille, P. A." box="[296,475,1231,1257]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" refId="ref356313" refString="Latreille, P. A. (1802) Histoire naturelle, generale et particuliere, des crustaces et des insectes. Tome troisieme. Dufart, Paris, 467 pp." type="book" year="1802">Latreille (1802)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[487,671,1231,1257]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" pagination="63 - 112" refId="ref368107" refString="Rondani, C. (1848 b) Esame di varie specie d'insetti ditteri brasiliani. Studi Entomologici, 1 (1), 63 - 112, pl. IIIbis." type="journal article" year="1848">Rondani (1848b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rondani, C." box="[682,752,1230,1257]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" pagination="165 - 197" refId="ref368231" refString="Rondani, C. (1850 c) Osservazioni sopra alquante specie di esapodi ditteri del Museo Torinese. Nuovi Annali delle Scienze Naturali e Rendiconto delle Sessioni della Societa Agraria e dell'Accademia delle Scienze dell'Istituto di Bologna, Series 3, 2, 165 - 197, 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1850">1850c</bibRefCitation>
) described two Neotropical species, both considered as valid (
<bibRefCitation author="James, M. T." box="[159,296,1267,1294]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref354589" refString="James, M. T. (1968) Family Rhagionidae (Leptidae). In: Papavero, N. (Ed.), A catalogue of the Diptera of the Americas south of the United States. Departamento de Zoologia, Secretaria de Agricultura, Sao Paulo, 29, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1968">James 1968</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectingRegion box="[316,395,1267,1293]" country="New Zealand" name="Nelson" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Nelson</collectingRegion>
Papavero examined the 
<collectionCode box="[672,751,1267,1293]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">MRSN</collectionCode>
<typeStatus box="[758,806,1267,1293]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">type</typeStatus>
material without publishing any results. The 
<typeStatus box="[1317,1365,1267,1293]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1848" box="[226,390,1303,1329]" genus="Leptis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="181" pageNumber="182" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis box="[226,390,1303,1329]" italics="true" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">Leptis apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has presumably been lost, the 
<typeStatus box="[734,782,1303,1329]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">type</typeStatus>
material of the other species is in the 
<collectionCode box="[1208,1291,1303,1329]" pageId="181" pageNumber="182">MRSN</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
